article.headline: Alabama St. 65, Southern U. 46
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) -- Brandon Gordon had 13 points to lead Alabama State to an easy 65-46 win over Southern University Monday night. The Hornets led 34-17 at the half and widened their margin in the second half. Joel Bosh had 12 points for Alabama State and Brandon Brooks and Richard Lott, Jr. added 10 points apiece. Brooks also had 12 assists. With 10 points Chris Davis was the only Southern player to score in double digits.
